WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.270 --> 00:00:14.190
I am Komatsu Akihito, I was born as Prince
Yoshiaki and Considered a brilliant military

2
00:00:14.190 --> 00:00:15.590
tactician.

3
00:00:15.590 --> 00:00:19.539
I am the seventh son of Prince Fushimi Kuniie.

4
00:00:19.539 --> 00:00:25.230
In 1858, I was adopted by Emperor Ninko as
a potential heir to the throne.

5
00:00:25.230 --> 00:00:31.250
I served in Kyoto under a Buddhist priesthood
and later returned to secular life in 1867

6
00:00:31.250 --> 00:00:37.620
during the Meiji Restoration, and led imperial
forces to Osaka, Yamato, Shikoku and Aizu

7
00:00:37.620 --> 00:00:41.750
during the Boshin War to overthrow the Tokugawa
shogunate.

8
00:00:41.750 --> 00:00:47.280
I helped subdue many of the samurai rebellions
in the early years of the Meiji period, including

9
00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:53.760
the Saga Rebellion of 1874, and the Satsuma
Rebellion of 1877.

10
00:00:53.760 --> 00:00:58.690
The emperor granted me the rank of lieutenant
general in the newly created Imperial Japanese

11
00:00:58.690 --> 00:01:02.090
Army and awarded me the Order of the Rising
Sun.

12
00:01:02.090 --> 00:01:07.460
I rose to the rank of general and received
command of the First Imperial Guard Division

13
00:01:07.460 --> 00:01:08.650
in 1890.

14
00:01:08.650 --> 00:01:14.409
I was nominal commander of the Japanese expeditionary
forces in the First Sino-Japanese War and

15
00:01:14.409 --> 00:01:19.181
became a member of the Supreme Military Council
and later became the chief of the Imperial

16
00:01:19.181 --> 00:01:24.359
Japanese Army General Staff, and received
the honorary rank of field marshal.

17
00:01:24.359 --> 00:01:29.240
In my latter years, I was a patron of the
Japanese Red Cross Society along with other

18
00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:33.920
charity institutions until I died peacefully
in 1898.

19
00:01:33.920 --> 00:01:38.880
I fought with great faith in my beloved Japan
and hope this has contributed to a prosperous

20
00:01:38.880 --> 00:01:39.859
and blooming nation.

